content:
Compare Standard and Enhanced WhatsApp Channel Capabilities

View a side-by-side comparison of standard and enhanced WhatsApp channels. Going forward, new features are available exclusively in enhanced WhatsApp channels.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience. View required editions

IMPORTANT Standard WhatsApp channels are scheduled for retirement in mid-2025 due to changes in the WhatsApp API, and as of July 1, 2024, you canâ€™t create new standard WhatsApp channels. To avoid service interruptions, upgrade your standard WhatsApp channels to enhanced channels before July 30, 2025.

CAPABILITY	STANDARD WHATSAPP	ENHANCED WHATSAPP
Setup and Routing	
Automated channel setup	No	Yes
Omni-Channel Flow routing	Yes	Yes
Queue-based routing	Yes	Yes
Enhanced routing	No	Yes

Messaging Session Start and End	
Customer can start session	Yes	Yes
Agent can start session	Yes, via the Start Conversation quick action (beta)	Yes, via the Send Message global action

Customer Experience	
Typing indicator: customer side	No	No
Delivered receipts: agent side	No	No

Agent Experience	
Quick text	Yes	Yes
Message templates	Yes	Yes
Einstein recommended replies	No	Yes

Content Sharing	
File sharing	Yes	Yes
Text	Yes, up to 1,600 characters	Yes, up to 4,096 characters.

Images	Yes, up to 5 MB: .jpg, .jpeg, .png. Yes, up to 5 MB inbound and 25 MB outbound: .jpeg, .png.

PDFs	Yes, up to 5 MB	Yes, up to 30 MB inbound and 25 MB outbound.

Documents	No	Yes, up to 30 MB inbound and 25 MB outbound: .txt, .ppt, .pptx, .pps, .ppsx, .doc, .docx, .xls, .xlsx, .csv.

Audio files	No	Yes, up to 16 MB inbound and 25 MB outbound: .aac, .amr.

Video files	No	Yes, up to 16 MB inbound and 25 MB outbound: .mp4, .3gp.

Automated Responses	
Conversation acknowledgment	Yes	Yes
End session	Yes	Yes

Security and Consent Management	
Sensitive data rules	Yes	Yes
Customers can opt out	Yes	Yes
title: Service Cloud: Compare Standard and Enhanced WhatsApp Channels
